          <declname>Channel</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function returns interrupt status read from Interrupt Status Register. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Use the XCSUDMA_IXR_*_MASK constants defined in <ref refid="xcsudma__hw_8h" kindref="compound">xcsudma_hw.h</ref> to interpret the returned value.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to <ref refid="struct_x_csu_dma" kindref="compound">XCsuDma</ref> instance to be worked on. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Channel</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Type of channel Source channel - XCSUDMA_SRC_CHANNEL Destination Channel - XCSUDMA_DST_CHANNEL</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>The pending interrupts of the CSU_DMA. Use th following masks to interpret the returned value. XCSUDMA_IXR_SRC_MASK - For Source channel XCSUDMA_IXR_DST_MASK - For Destination channel</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>None. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
