      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__csuma__api_1ga1db5eabd96920efb06fb03c919420601" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void XCsuDma_IntrClear</definition>
        <argsstring>(XCsuDma *InstancePtr, XCsuDma_Channel Channel, u32 Mask)</argsstring>
        <name>XCsuDma_IntrClear</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_x_csu_dma" kindref="compound">XCsuDma</ref> *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="group__csuma__api_1ga46008337fdd632f2650b8727c305eba5" kindref="member">XCsuDma_Channel</ref></type>
          <declname>Channel</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>u32</type>
          <declname>Mask</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function clears interrupt(s). </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Every bit set in Interrupt Status Register indicates that a specific type of interrupt is occurring, and this function clears one or more interrupts by writing a bit mask to Interrupt Clear Register.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to <ref refid="struct_x_csu_dma" kindref="compound">XCsuDma</ref> instance to be worked on. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Channel</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Type of channel Source channel - XCSUDMA_SRC_CHANNEL Destination Channel - XCSUDMA_DST_CHANNEL </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Mask</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Mask to clear. Bit positions of 1 will be cleared. Bit positions of 0 will not change the previous interrupt status. This mask is formed by OR&apos;ing XCSUDMA_IXR_* bits defined in <ref refid="xcsudma__hw_8h" kindref="compound">xcsudma_hw.h</ref>.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>None. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
